---
import BaseLayout from "../../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import MetricCard from "../../../components/MetricCard.astro";
---

<BaseLayout>

<article class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">

<header class="mb-14">

<h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold mb-4">
Activity Channel Manager
</h1>

<p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">
Refactoring and evolution of the activity distribution system,
connecting tourism activity providers with major international
distribution platforms.
</p>

</header>


<!-- METRICS -->

<div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-4 mb-10">

<MetricCard value="5" label="distribution platforms integrated" />

<MetricCard value="Millions" label="reservations processed" />

<MetricCard value="Full" label="system refactor" />

</div>


<!-- DESCRIPTION -->

<section class="mb-12">

<p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 mb-4">
The channel manager allows activity providers to distribute their
products across multiple tourism marketplaces while maintaining
centralized control over availability, pricing and booking
synchronization.
</p>

<p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">
The system was progressively refactored to improve maintainability
and scalability, applying clean architecture principles and
decoupling external integrations from the core business logic.
</p>

</section>


<!-- INTEGRATIONS -->

<section class="mb-12">

<h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4">
Distribution platforms
</h2>

<ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 list-disc pl-6">

<li>Civitatis</li>

<li>GetYourGuide</li>

<li>Viator</li>

<li>Tiqets (OCTO protocol)</li>

<li>Axess</li>

</ul>

</section>


<!-- ARCHITECTURE -->

<section>

<h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4">
Technical highlights
</h2>

<ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 list-disc pl-6">

<li>Large scale API integrations with tourism distribution platforms</li>

<li>Refactoring applying Clean Code and Hexagonal Architecture</li>

<li>Improved maintainability of external integrations</li>

<li>Scalable architecture for adding new distribution channels</li>

</ul>

</section>


</article>

</BaseLayout>